		<pb n="1"/>
			<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>San Francisco</placeName> <date>March 1.&#47;54</date></p>
			<p><addressee>Mr. Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">Dear Friend&#8212;</p>
			<p>Hardly anything of any interest<lb/> has transpired since my last<lb/> Letter&#44; which might serve You as a<lb/> Matter of News&#59; however I will drop<lb/> a few Lines to you&#44; to inform you of<lb/> a Ball to be given by the &#8220;Hebrew<lb/> Benevolent Society&#44;&#8221; on next &#8220;<date>Purim</date>&#8221;<lb/> which promises so far to be a fine<lb/> affair&#59; a large number of tickets<lb/> have already been disposed&#44; and the<lb/> managers make active preparations<lb/> to get up a Ball <sic>praiseworty</sic> of the<lb/> society&#59; the tickets are sold at &#36;10. The Emani El Congregation<lb/> had drawn several plans for a<lb/> synagogue&#44; &#38; have chosen one&#44; &#38; are now<lb/> about giving out proposals&#59; the plan prescribes<lb/> the Gothic style&#44; &#38; when finished will be<lb/> one of the finest synagogues in the <placeName>United<lb/> States</placeName>&#59; the Building will be about 50 x 80 feet.<lb/> &#8220;Mazos&#8221; will be sold at 22&#162; pr. pound<lb/> The baking of it will shortly be begun.</p>
		<pb n="2"/>
			<p><persName>Mr. &#38; Mrs. Roggenburger</persName> give their best<lb/> Respects to you&#59; &#38; Hoping this will find<lb/> you in good spirits &#38; Health</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">I remain yours Truly</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)"><persName role="author">Cauffman H. Meyer</persName></p>
			<p>P.S. You will have recd a Letter from the<lb/> sec. of the Em. congregation about a chason &#38;<lb/> the advertisement</p>
         
